rk event kicks off with heavy product demonstration also including company’s new cable box tony maglio  september     am brian l roberts has some neat new toys for comcast’s xfinity customers and he used lots of stage time on tuesday to brag about ‘em the chairman and chief executive officer was up early at goldman sachs communacopia — the very first panel of the conference actually after the requisite praising of nbc broadcast for winning another week season and declaring his film arm — which recently purchased dreamworks animation — to be “in great shape” roberts wanted to do a little demo that little demo turned into a lot of it first up was the x settop box and its remote voice recognition’s integration into netflix roberts spent quite a bit of time showing off that one debuting his shared interface and some of the cooler features one can seamlessly control also read nbcuniversal to cut  dreamworks animation jobs but as they say in showbiz that’s not all roberts boasted a bit later about his new xi wireless cable box which is all wifi based and has khdr capabilities right now it’s meant for additional tvs in one’s home but soon he believes the little guy will replace your primary one “i think this is the future of how we’re making cable boxes” roberts said of the small device declaring it “the best cable box we’ve ever made” also read nbcuniversal ceo steve burke wants to bring you more sequels of course that means one needs excellent and reliable wifi roberts then pulled out the xb which also handles telephone and broadband needs “the world’s fastest router” were his words of praise for that one lest you think we’re nitpicking or exaggerating about exactly how roberts used much of his  minutes btig analyst rich greenfield tweeted the following midway during the panel comcasts brian roberts hosting a  minute netflix infomercial – demo’ing integration into x settop box nflx cmcsa pictwittercomovfpae — rich greenfield richbtig september    people you never expecte