he philadelphia ers nbabasketball team and two large multipurpose arenas in philadelphia mr roberts is a member of the board of directors of the national cable  telecommunications association ncta where he served as chairman for two consecutive terms from  he also served as nctas chairman from  when the landmark deregulatory  telecommunications act became law mr roberts is serving his third term as chairman of cablelabs the research and development consortium for the cable industry he previously served as their chair from  and  mr roberts has won numerous business and industry honors for his leadership in january of  institutional investor magazine named him as one of americas top ceos for the fifth year in a row also in  he was recognized by big brothers and big sisters for his outstanding leadership in the community and for serving as a role model to youth in may  he was presented with the cable industry’s highest honor the distinguished vanguard award for leadership in october of  he was inducted into the cable television hall of fame in  he was honored by the national association for multiethnicity in communications namic for his commitment to diversity in the cable industry and by the partnership for a drugfree america for comcasts unprecedented commitment of resources to champion the pdfas drugfree message he also was the recipient of the  humanitarian award from the simon wiesenthal center in  mr roberts was awarded the steven j ross humanitarian award by the uja federation of new york in  he was honored by the police athletic league of philadelphia for his commitment to youth programs and community partnerships mr roberts cochaired the  resource development campaign for the united way of southeastern pennsylvania and was a founding cochair of philadelphia  the nonpartisan host committee for the  republican national convention an allamerican in squash he earned a gold medal with the us squash team in  and silver medals at the   and  maccabiah games in israel 